<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="300" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d300">
                    <head>300. Central Intelligence Agency General Order No. 10<note n="0" type="source" xml:id="d300fn0">Source: Central Intelligence Agency
                            Historical Files, HS/CSG–2155, Job 83–00739R, Box 3, Folder 20.
                            Secret.</note></head>
                    <dateline><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-27">August 27, 1948</date>.</dateline>
                    <list type="subject">
                        <head>SUBJECT</head>
                        <item>Organization</item>
                    </list>
                    <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>The activation of the Office of Policy Coordination, effective 1
                            September 1948, is hereby announced.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>Mr. <persName corresp="#p_WFG1">Frank G. Wisner</persName> is
                            announced as Assistant Director for Policy Coordination.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Detailed directives reference the functions of the Office of Policy
                            Coordination will be the subject of separate orders.</item>
                    </list>
                    <closer>For the Director of Central Intelligence:<lb/><signed><persName corresp="#p_WCEK1"><hi rend="strong">E. K.
                            Wright</hi></persName></signed><lb/><hi rend="italic">Brigadier General,
                            USA <lb/> Deputy Director</hi></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>